<div class="simple-footnotes"><p class="notes">Notes:</p><ol><li id="note-29121-1">&#8220;<a href="http://is.gd/ZLI2T2">So live in the present moment most of the time – perhaps 95-99% of it</a>.</p>
<p>But plan for the future in the 1-5% of your time that can have an impact out of all proportion to the time.  When it comes to those decisions, stop smelling the roses.   Think as carefully as you possibly can.   Heighten your instincts.  Seek help in making the right decision.  Be utterly mindful.  Be as skillful as you possibly can.  And be utterly committed to the decision.</p>
<p>Let most decisions – the unimportant ones – take care of themselves.&#8221;</p>
